JOHANNESBURG - Government has reached an agreement with construction companies after being found to have participated in corrupt tender processes. The construction giants include Group Five, WBHO, Basil Read, Stefanutti Stocks, Aveng and Murray and Roberts. READ:Â Competition Commission slaps construction giants with additional fine The companies will sell at least 40 percent of their shares to black people, or help black owned companies grow their businesses. The agreement will be part of an overall R1.4-billion fine imposed by the Competition Tribunal. This commitment has been valued in excess of R9-billion. eNCA